paragraphs.text:
run(sql="

with cte as(
    select a.subOrderId, b.nm from `temp.final_attri2` a left join `all(unitEconomicsBaseTable)` b
    on a.subOrderId = b.subOrderId
    where DATEDIFF(CURRENT_DATE(),TO_DATE(FROM_UNIXTIME(b.timestamp/1000))) BETWEEN 1 AND 50
),

cte2 as(
    select cte.subOrderId, cte.nm, b.pogId, b.productName, b.categoryGroup 
    from cte left join `all(agCmDump)` b
    on cte.subOrderId=b.subOrderId
    where DATEDIFF(CURRENT_DATE(),TO_DATE(FROM_UNIXTIME(b.orderDate/1000))) BETWEEN 1 AND 50
)

select * 
from (
select productName, pogId, categoryGroup,count(distinct subOrderId) as orders, sum(nm) as nm_total, ROW_NUMBER() OVER (ORDER BY count(distinct subOrderId) DESC) AS rn 
    from cte2
    where sum(nm)>=40
    group by productName, pogId, categoryGroup
    order by orders desc
)
where rn<500


",1000)

paragraphs.title: Based on NM
paragraphs.text:
run(sql="
with cte as(
    select row_number() over(order by sum(ue.nm) DESC) as rn,ag.productName
            ,ag.pogId
            ,COUNT(DISTINCT ag.subOrderId) AS subo
            ,sum(ue.nm) as total_nm
    from (
                    select DISTINCT TO_DATE(FROM_UNIXTIME(orderDate/1000)) as order_date,productName, pogId, subOrderId
                    from `all(agCmDump)` 
                    where DATEDIFF(CURRENT_DATE(),TO_DATE(FROM_UNIXTIME(orderDate/1000))) BETWEEN 1 AND 15
                    and categoryGroup = 'Home & Kitchen'
                )ag
    left join (
                    select DISTINCT subOrderId, nm from `all(unitEconomicsBaseTable)`)ue
    on ag.subOrderId=ue.subOrderId
    GROUP BY productName
            ,pogId
    ORDER BY total_nm DESC)
select productName, pogId, total_nm from cte where rn<51

",1000)
